modules.description: Processes UTF-8 encoded strings by iterating over each character and its position, applying a folding function that handles malformed sequences or valid Unicode code points. Operates on strings and uses a custom folder type to accumulate results during traversal. Useful for parsing or transforming encoded text while tracking character positions and handling invalid data.

Decodes various character encodings including UTF-7, ISO-8859, and KOI8 into Unicode code points, supporting conversion to UTF-8 via uutf. Processes encoded-word structures from email messages as specified in RFC 2047. Accepts custom encodings by integrating new libraries through issue tracking.

Processes UTF-8 encoded strings by traversing each character and its index, applying a folding function that either handles malformed sequences or processes valid Unicode code points. It uses a custom folder type to accumulate results during iteration, enabling precise control over text transformation or analysis. This allows for tasks like validating encoding, extracting specific characters, or building structured data from raw text. Examples include counting valid code points, detecting invalid sequences, or generating position-aware output.
